        "Name": "Kingfisher X",
        "Details": "An early Clan assault OmniMech that may have influenced all subsequent assault OmniMech design, the Kingfisher is rugged and maneuverable. These traits make the Kingfisher an ideal choice for take and hold missions.<br>Based off the powerful but dezgra Pulverizer, Clan Snow Raven debuted the Kingfisher in 2887 as an early second-generation OmniMech. The Kingfisher's speed and relative durability have kept it in heavy use even during the Clan Invasion era, especially by Clan Ghost Bear, alongside more recent assault OmniMechs like the Executioner.<br>This variant of the Kingfisher has been redesigned by an unnamed clan to use an XL engine, freeing up more tonnage for weaponry.<br><br>X-class mechs feature upgrades to their armour and defensive systems that improve their survivability on the 31st century battlefield.",
